%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20you're%20probably%20not%20going%20to%20like%20what%20I%20have%20to%20say%20about%20remote%20work%3A%20Most%20employees%2C%20especially%20young-tenured%20employees%2C%20should%20work%20in%20the%20office%20instead%20of%20from%20home.%20But%20in%20order%20to%20fully%20benefit%20from%20in-office%20work%2C%20young-tenured%20employees%20also%20need%20experienced%20employees%20to%20work%20in%20the%20office%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20before%20the%20pitchforks%20come%20for%20me%2C%20I'm%20100%25%20supportive%20of%20remote%20work%20and%20I'm%20fully%20supportive%20of%20employee%20flexibility%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-work-from-home-benefits-as-good-as-raise-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20the%20great%20things%20that%20come%20with%20working%20remotely%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20while%20many%20people%20talk%20about%20the%20benefits%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwfh-workers-less-efficient-than-people-in-office-new-research-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efew%20talk%20about%20its%20consequences.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20in-person%20is%20more%20collaborative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20the%20start%20of%20my%20career%20back%20in%201999%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20an%20office%2C%20side-by-side%20with%20other%20co-workers%20and%20we'd%20frequently%20diagram%20problems%20on%20the%20office%20whiteboard.%20I%20could%20turn%20my%20chair%20around%20and%20talk%20to%20my%20team%20members%20that%20were%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%20right%20next%20to%20me.%20As%20a%20quality%20assurance%20engineer%2C%20I%20could%20quickly%20show%20the%20software%20developers%20an%20error%20that%20I%20was%20seeing%20on%20my%20screen.%20While%20it%20sounds%20like%20an%20environment%20full%20of%20disruptions%2C%20it%20wasn't%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20us%20worked%20very%20well%20together%20and%20respected%20each%20other's%20ways%20of%20working.%20We%20worked%20hard%2C%20we%20moved%20fast%2C%20we%20collaborated%20with%20ease%2C%20and%20we%20got%20results.%20Also%2C%20everyone%20learned%20a%20lot%20because%20they%20had%20direct%20and%20quick%20access%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20could%20eavesdrop%20and%20learn%20in-person%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20better%20or%20worse%2C%20everyone%20also%20had%20access%20to%20overhear%20conversations%20that%20others%20were%20having.%20This%20was%20sometimes%20disruptive%20when%20a%20co-worker%20was%20speaking%20too%20loudly%2C%20but%20overhearing%20conversations%20had%20benefits%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accidental%20eavesdropping%20allowed%20team%20members%20to%20hear%20about%20topics%20that%20they%20otherwise%20would%20have%20been%20excluded%20from.%20This%20increased%20the%20spread%20of%20ideas%20and%20knowledge%2C%20and%20for%20team%20members%20to%20interject%20a%20comment%20of%20related%20work%20being%20performed%20by%20other%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaders%20are%20more%20accessible%20in-person%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20leader%2C%20being%20in%20the%20office%20also%20allowed%20me%20to%20better%20assess%20the%20skills%20and%20knowledge%20of%20my%20direct%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20see%20first-hand%20how%20they%20communicated%2C%20interacted%2C%20and%20helped%20stakeholders%20and%20more%20junior%20members%20of%20the%20team.%20This%20not%20only%20provided%20me%20with%20perspective%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20write%20their%20annual%20reviews%2C%20but%20it%20allowed%20me%20to%20give%20in-the-moment%20coaching.%20It%20also%20allowed%20me%20to%20provide%20additional%20coaching%20and%20support%20during%20our%20weekly%201%3A1%20meeting.%20But%20the%20benefits%20didn't%20stop%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20sitting%20next%20to%20my%20team%20members%2C%20I%20was%20accessible%2C%20and%20they%20were%20accessible.%20When%20I%20found%20something%20interesting%20that%20was%20worth%20sharing%20with%20the%20team%2C%20I%20could%20physically%20turn%20around%20and%20quickly%20share%20information%20to%20elevate%20my%20team%20members.%20My%20team%20members%20could%20also%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20waiting%20to%20book%20a%20meeting%20on%20my%20calendar%20or%20spending%20excessive%20amounts%20of%20time%20solving%20a%20problem%2C%20they%20could%20simply%20ask%20me.%20By%20having%20direct%20access%2C%20they%20weren't%20left%20guessing%20and%20implementing%20changes%20without%20feedback%20and%20validation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20in-office%20interactions%20and%20physical%20proximity%20to%20each%20other%2C%20we%20would%20have%20created%20more%20bugs%20in%20our%20software%2C%20built%20things%20that%20other%20teams%20had%20already%20built%2C%20and%20slowed%20the%20dissemination%20of%20ideas%20and%20knowledge.%20This%20would%20have%20led%20to%20a%20slowdown%20in%20growth%20to%20the%20company%20as%20well%20as%20individual%20skills%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemote%20work%20creates%20inefficiencies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20my%20experience%2C%20slower%20growth%20is%20happening%20for%20many%20employees%20because%20they%20aren't%20overhearing%20these%20valuable%20conversations%2C%20and%20they%20aren't%20able%20to%20receive%20help%20from%20co-workers%20or%20managers%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20leading%20to%20duplication%20of%20work%20and%20less%20collaboration%2C%20along%20with%20leadership%20challenges%20with%20being%20able%20to%20assess%20the%20skills%20of%20team%20members%20properly.%20I've%20witnessed%20frequent%20situations%20where%20team%20members%20are%20reinventing%20the%20wheel%20due%20to%20reduced%20communication%20related%20to%20remote%20work.%20This%20is%20a%20problem%20that%20existed%20before%20remote%20work%2C%20but%20to%20a%20lesser%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20remote%20work%2C%20communication%20is%20also%20slowed%20as%20many%20team%20members%20err%20on%20the%20side%20of%20politeness.%20This%20means%20that%20when%20problems%20occur%2C%20employees%20book%20time%20on%20another%20employee's%20calendar%20instead%20of%20simply%20turning%20to%20the%20person%20next%20to%20them%20or%20walking%20down%20the%20hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20would%20have%20taken%205%20minutes%20to%20address%20in%20an%20in-office%20environment%20has%20now%20been%20delayed%20hours%20or%20even%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20not%20only%20slows%20down%20progress%20for%20the%20employee%20and%20company%2C%20but%20it%20also%20creates%20additional%20inefficiencies.%20Without%20rapid%20responses%2C%20in-the-moment%20details%20are%20forgotten%20or%20require%20time-consuming%20documentation%20that%20will%20be%20needed%20for%20the%20upcoming%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeaders%20are%20disadvantaged%20as%20well%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20management%20standpoint%2C%20leaders%20lose%20exposure%20to%20their%20team%20members%20%E2%80%94%20they%20no%20longer%20get%20to%20see%20personal%20interactions%2C%20where%20people%20are%20getting%20stuck%20or%20becoming%20stressed.%20I'm%20not%20suggesting%20that%20leaders%20are%20or%20were%20micromanaging%2C%20but%20these%20small%20things%20are%20crucial%20to%20being%20able%20to%20understand%20and%20elevate%20team%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20leader%2C%20my%20job%20is%20to%20create%20opportunities%20for%20team%20members%20to%20succeed%2C%20but%20also%20to%20be%20challenged.%20Without%20more%20interaction%2C%20I%20can't%20help%20and%20elevate%20my%20team%20as%20quickly%20as%20I%20would%20like%20or%20as%20quickly%20as%20they%20deserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20suggest%20that%20employees%20need%20to%20speak%20up%20more%20when%20they%20are%20struggling%20or%20run%20into%20an%20issue.%20But%20this%20isn't%20very%20realistic%20and%20doesn't%20get%20to%20the%20root%20of%20the%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdmitting%20mistakes%20or%20failures%20can%20be%20a%20hard%20pill%20to%20swallow%2C%20and%20sharing%20this%20information%20to%20anyone%20can%20be%20embarrassing%20and%20even%20risky%20for%20your%20career.%20Also%2C%20struggling%20employees%20might%20not%20realize%20that%20they%20are%20struggling%20until%20seeing%20a%20colleague%20do%20something%20more%20efficiently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThese%20problems%20are%20only%20going%20to%20multiply%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERemote%20work%20isn't%20going%20away%20and%20unfortunately%20the%20problems%20of%20remote%20work%20and%20distributed%20teams%20will%20multiply%20as%20we%20go%20forward.%20To%20solve%20these%20problems%2C%20we%20need%20company%20leaders%20to%20acknowledge%20what%20employees%20desire%2C%20provide%20empathy%20and%20transparency%2C%20have%20open%20dialogue%2C%20and%20search%20for%20better%20solutions%20for%20remote%20and%20distributed%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20given%20the%20choice%20to%20work%20remotely%20or%20in-person%2C%20employees%20should%20work%20together%20in%20the%20office%20to%20increase%20their%20ability%20to%20effectively%20communicate%2C%20learn%20from%20others%2C%20and%20create%20important%20relationships%20for%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20doing%20so%2C%20these%20employees%20will%20likely%20increase%20their%20knowledge%20and%20chances%20for%20increased%20scope%20of%20work%2C%20which%20are%20the%20foundations%20for%20raises%20and%20promotions%20in%20the%20workplace.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%20He%20also%20creates%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40analyticsmentor%3F_t%3D8cgBuY7EINK%26_r%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETikToks%20about%20data%20analytics%20and%20career%20development%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20