s%20at%20the%20lunch%20sent%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20to%20headquarters%20in%20Islamabad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20discussions%2C%20as%20per%20the%20note%20published%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EIntercept%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Lu%20conveyed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20unhappiness%20over%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20policy%20on%20Ukraine.%20Russia%20had%20begun%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20on%20February%2024%2C%20just%20as%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20enroute%20Moscow%20on%20a%20state%20visit.%20Thereafter%2C%20Pakistan%20had%20also%20abstained%20on%20various%20UN%20resolutions%20that%20criticised%20Russia%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20note%20stated%20that%20Lu%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cquite%20clear%20that%20this%20is%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20policy%E2%80%9D%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20military%20establishment%20was%20not%20on%20the%20same%20page.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELu%20added%20that%20the%20view%20was%20that%20this%20policy%20over%20Russia%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctied%20to%20the%20current%20political%20dramas%20in%20Islamabad%20that%20he%20(Prime%20Minister)%20needs%20and%20is%20trying%20to%20show%20a%20public%20face%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Pakistani%20ambassador%20apparently%20responded%20that%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20correct%20reading%20of%20the%20developments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20following%20key%20excerpt%20from%20the%20diplomatic%20cable%20is%20where%20Lu%20refers%20to%20the%20disenchantment%20over%20Khan.%20He%20conveyed%2C%20as%20per%20the%20version%20transcribed%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%2C%20that%20if%20Khan%20lost%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%2C%20it%20will%20be%20easier%20for%20US%20and%20its%20western%20allies%20to%20quickly%20mend%20frayed%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Pakistan%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20asked%20Don%20if%20the%20reason%20for%20a%20strong%20U.S.%20reaction%20was%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20abstention%20in%20the%20voting%20in%20the%20UNGA.%20He%20categorically%20replied%20in%20the%20negative%20and%20said%20that%20it%20was%20due%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Moscow.%20He%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20if%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%20against%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20succeeds%2C%20all%20will%20be%20forgiven%20in%20Washington%20because%20the%20Russia%20visit%20is%20being%20looked%20at%20as%20a%20decision%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%20Otherwise%2C%20I%20think%20it%20will%20be%20tough%20going%20ahead.%E2%80%9D%20He%20paused%20and%20then%20said%20%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20tell%20how%20this%20will%20be%20seen%20by%20Europe%20but%20I%20suspect%20their%20reaction%20will%20be%20similar.%E2%80%9D%20He%20then%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Chonestly%20I%20think%20isolation%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20will%20become%20very%20strong%20from%20Europe%20and%20the%20United%20States.%E2%80%9D%20Don%20further%20commented%20that%20it%20seemed%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Moscow%20was%20planned%20during%20the%20Beijing%20Olympics%20and%20there%20was%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20meet%20Putin%20which%20was%20not%20successful%20and%20then%20this%20idea%20was%20hatched%20that%20he%20would%20go%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20another%20part%20of%20the%20published%20cable%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20accused%20the%20US%20of%20being%20tougher%20on%20Pakistan%20while%20going%20easy%20on%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20had%20also%20taken%20a%20neutral%20position%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDon%20was%20evasive%20and%20responded%20that%20Washington%20looked%20at%20the%20U.S.-India%20relationship%20very%20much%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20China.%20He%20added%20that%20while%20India%20had%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20Moscow%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20we%20will%20actually%20see%20a%20change%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20once%20all%20Indian%20students%20are%20out%20of%20Ukraine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20article%20also%20said%20that%20the%20document%20was%20%E2%80%9Cprovided%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EIntercept%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20an%20anonymous%20source%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20military%20who%20said%20that%20they%20had%20no%20ties%20to%20Imran%20Khan%20or%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20party%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Pakistan%20government%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20ended%20at%20Wednesday%20midnight%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRanaSanaullahPK%2Fstatus%2F1689354884762710016%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERana%20Sanaullah%20Khan%2C%20interior%20minister%20in%20Shahbaz%20Sharif%20cabinet%2C%20tweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20had%20to%20be%20an%20investigation%20to%20establish%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20document.%20%E2%80%9CPotentially%2C%20it%20is%20a%20very%20sinister%2C%20treacherous%2C%20and%20seditious%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThough%20there%20is%20nothing%20new%20in%20this%20story%2C%20the%20investigation%20needs%20to%20held%20to%20establish%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20information%20or%20source%20document.%20Potentially%2C%20it%20is%20a%20very%20sinister%2C%20treacherous%2C%20and%20seditious%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(1%2F2)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rana%20SanaUllah%20Khan%20(%40RanaSanaullahPK)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRanaSanaullahPK%2Fstatus%2F1689354884762710016%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInd