ncies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20NASA%20stays%20away%20from%20sex%20and%20reproduction%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehnhardt%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20truly%20relevant%20to%20the%20work%20that%20we're%20doing%20at%20NASA%20right%20now%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20it%20has%20been%20relevant%2C%20reproductive%20health%20hasn't%20been%20one%20of%20NASA's%20strong%20suits.%20Engineers%20there%20famously%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsally-ride-first-american-woman-in-space-life-legacy-2019-6%5C%22%3Eastronaut%20Sally%20Ride%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20100%20tampons%20would%20be%20enough%20for%20a%20one-week%20spaceflight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20space%20reproduction%20studies%20that%20do%20exist%20are%20focused%20on%20rodents.%20Their%20findings%20may%20not%20be%20applicable%20to%20humans%20at%20all%2C%20but%20they%20offer%20hints%20that%20reproductive%20functions%20could%20be%20affected%20by%20space%20radiation%20and%20microgravity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colonel%20Walter%20Villadei%20aboard%20Galactic%2001%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3ab8182eb770019b9062d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColonel%20Walter%20Villadei%20floats%20in%20microgravity%20during%20a%20Virgin%20Galactic%20flight.%3Cp%3EVirgin%20Galactic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fnsr%2Farticle%2F7%2F9%2F1437%2F5819033%3Flogin%3Dfalse%23267959580%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20put%20mouse%20embryos%20in%20an%20incubator%20on%20board%20a%20satellite.%20The%20embryos%20developed%20in%20space%20but%20sustained%20%26quot%3Bsevere%26quot%3B%20DNA%20damage%20and%20had%20developmental%20defects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc36bbbfc6b6ba65038f24dad2830be619dba18ce4f0f5f96ab428388944151d6%26postID%3D646d4da3dff48323162199e6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41574-019-0267-6%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20exposure%20to%20microgravity%20decreased%20testosterone%C2%A0levels%20and%20sperm%20production%20in%20male%20rats.%20Some%20female%20rats%20have%20mated%20during%20spaceflight%20but%20then%20shown%20signs%20of%20early%20pregnancy%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20forms%20of%20radiation%20on%20Earth%20are%20known%20to%20have%20negative%20effects%20on%20human%20pregnancy.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthe%20galactic%20cosmic%20radiation%20that%20we%20experience%20in%20space%20doesn't%20have%20a%20good%20comparison%20on%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehnhardt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20even%20be%20risky%20to%20conceive%20within%20a%20few%20months%20of%20returning%20from%20spaceflight%2C%C2%A0the%20green%20paper%20authors%20argue.%20Again%2C%20research%20is%20lacking.%20The%20uncertainty%20is%20enough%20for%20some%20astronauts%20to%20freeze%20their%20eggs%20before%20they%20launch%20into%20orbit%2C%20according%20to%20Lehnhardt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHave%20you%20talked%20to%20your%20spaceflight%20customers%20about%20sex%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22elon%20musk%20raises%20one%20eyebrow%20wearing%20a%20suit%20in%20as%20room%20full%20of%20seated%20men%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3a7d411d6ad0019edfba6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BChoose%20France%26quot%3B%20Summit%20at%20the%20Chateau%20de%20Versailles%2C%20outside%20Paris.%3Cp%3ELudovic%20Marin%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20does%20get%20pregnant%20up%20there%2C%20that%20person%20or%20their%20fetus%20could%20face%20complications.%20Failure%20to%20address%20this%20possibility%20puts%20space-tourism%20companies%20at%20