%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20far%20as%20we%20know%2C%20SpaceX%20is%20not%20discussing%20sex%20with%20its%20spaceflight%20customers.%3Cp%3EGonzalo%20Fuentes%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Cullen%20and%20other%20authors%20of%20the%20paper%20are%20working%20on%20an%20initiative%20called%20SpaceBorn%20United%2C%20to%20research%20in%20vitro%20fertilization%20(IVF)%20in%20space.%20The%20company%20plans%20to%20try%20space%20IVF%20first%20using%20mouse%20embryos%2C%20in%202024%2C%20but%20eventually%20aims%20to%20test%20on%20human%20embyros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20stepping%20stones%20of%20research%20that%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20see%20how%20viable%20pregnancy%20could%20be%20in%20the%20space%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehnhardt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20he%20was%20sure%20to%20note%2C%20%26quot%3BNASA%20has%20absolutely%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-tourists-sex-pregnancy-risk-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691624577000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646e741ca739dc00180942fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-tourists-sex-pregnancy-risk-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20space%20tourism%20industry%20is%20growing%20up%20fast%2C%20and%20researchers%20say%20companies%20like%20SpaceX%20need%20to%20have%20the%20sex%20talk.%20NASA%20won't%20do%20it%20for%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40insider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A102%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-tourists-sex-pregnancy-risk-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elaine%20Frontain%20Bryant%2C%20Eli%20Lehrer%20Take%20On%20Expanded%20Roles%2